33:12.166 --> 33:14.633
♪ Somewhere out walkin' ♪

33:14.633 --> 33:16.400
♪ After midnight ♪

33:16.400 --> 33:22.567
♪ Searchin' for me ♪♪

33:23.767 --> 33:25.633
Arthur Godfrey:
Patsy Cline!

33:25.633 --> 33:27.033
Bravo!

33:27.033 --> 33:29.433
This Virginia gal can sing.

33:29.433 --> 33:32.300
Now let us hear from you
through the applause meter.

33:32.300 --> 33:33.467
Watch the meter now.

33:33.467 --> 33:35.467
Come on, people, clap louder!

33:35.467 --> 33:36.834
Go, go, go, go!

33:36.834 --> 33:38.700
(cheering and applause)

33:38.700 --> 33:41.300
Patsy Cline is the winner!

33:41.300 --> 33:44.066
Whoo!
She won!

33:44.066 --> 33:45.400
(applause)

33:49.867 --> 33:54.567
♪ I go out walkin'
after midnight ♪

33:54.567 --> 33:57.033
♪ Out in the moonlight ♪

33:57.033 --> 33:59.367
♪ Just hopin' you may be ♪

33:59.367 --> 34:03.567
♪ Somewhere out walkin'
after midnight ♪

34:03.567 --> 34:11.132
♪ Searchin' for me ♪

34:11.132 --> 34:12.766
Bull's eye!

34:12.766 --> 34:14.433
(sighs)

34:14.433 --> 34:16.667
That was draggy to me that
time, real draggy.

34:16.667 --> 34:18.000
Patsy, that's all right.
Shit.

34:18.000 --> 34:21.333
This is gonna make us all a
whole lot of money, little girl.

34:21.333 --> 34:23.632
Hey, listen, boys, you don't
mind if we just try it one--

34:23.632 --> 34:25.333
(all moaning)
Come on, one more time!

34:25.333 --> 34:28.433
(discord piano)
Thanks a lot, boys.

34:52.600 --> 34:54.934
(humming)

34:59.700 --> 35:02.133
♪ When you dance ♪

35:02.133 --> 35:06.867
♪ You'll squeeze her, yes,
with all your might ♪

35:06.867 --> 35:11.433
♪ Such a thrill to be
this close to you ♪

35:13.867 --> 35:15.900
I'm home, baby.

35:15.900 --> 35:17.200
Where have you been?

35:17.200 --> 35:18.700
I stopped and had a drink.

35:18.700 --> 35:21.033
Yeah, or five or seven.

35:21.033 --> 35:23.300
I worked my hump off
making you baked chicken.

35:23.300 --> 35:26.133
You come home this late.
I'll eat it.

35:26.133 --> 35:28.767
You got a finger?
Hmm? Yeah.

35:28.767 --> 35:30.400
Then use the goddamn thing.

35:30.400 --> 35:32.867
Put it in a telephone and dial
me when you're gonna be late.

35:32.867 --> 35:35.000
Look, I said I'd eat
the damn--

35:35.000 --> 35:37.066
Hey, lady, I got
a message for you.

35:37.066 --> 35:39.000
Screw your baked
chicken and screw you.

35:39.000 --> 35:40.233
Oh, yeah?!

35:40.233 --> 35:42.500
That's the last time I'm
gonna make you something nice.

35:42.500 --> 35:44.500
Oh, poor Patsy, boo-hoo-hoo.

35:44.500 --> 35:47.100
Oh, you dumb son of a bitch!

35:47.100 --> 35:48.467
You want your dinner?

35:48.467 --> 35:50.600
Here, why don't you eat it now?

35:50.600 --> 35:52.700
You want a plate?
You want a plate?

35:54.700 --> 35:57.100
(dishes, plates crashing)

35:57.100 --> 35:59.667
You wanna start on
the living room?

35:59.667 --> 36:01.967
(laughing)

36:01.967 --> 36:04.200
Charlie, look what
you've done!

36:04.200 --> 36:06.133
Goddamn it!

36:12.467 --> 36:14.367
(door opens)

36:17.867 --> 36:21.467
Sip it slow and the
world stays sweet.

36:21.467 --> 36:24.734
My daddy used to say
that same thing.

36:27.133 --> 36:29.567
Do my back, baby,
would you please?

36:32.166 --> 36:34.400
He was something,
my old man.

36:34.400 --> 36:36.633
He used to eat cold
navy bean sandwiches

36:36.633 --> 36:41.266
for breakfast every
morning of his life.

36:41.266 --> 36:43.333
I hope he rots in hell.

36:43.333 --> 36:45.533
What do you mean?

36:45.533 --> 36:47.867
He was crazy.

36:47.867 --> 36:50.166
He tried some
stuff with me once.

36:50.166 --> 36:52.667
You telling me he tried
to mess with you?

36:52.667 --> 36:54.400
(phone ringing)
Huh?

36:54.400 --> 36:56.533
Oh, Charlie, I don't want
to talk about that now.

36:56.533 --> 36:58.000
How come you never
told me that before?

36:58.000 --> 36:59.900
How come you never say
anything about your family?

36:59.900 --> 37:02.633
Well, not when I'm in
such a good mood.

37:02.633 --> 37:04.066
Hello?

37:04.066 --> 37:05.400
Patsy Cline?
Yeah, that's me.

37:05.400 --> 37:07.333
Charlie:
Who is it?
What?

37:07.333 --> 37:09.834
Is it Woodhouse?
Hey, Charlie, hush up.

37:09.834 --> 37:11.633
I'm sorry,
I didn't hear you.

37:11.633 --> 37:13.734
Tell him I got spanked 'cause
he made me late for dinner.

37:13.734 --> 37:15.734
Will you for the love of God,
put a lid on it!

37:15.734 --> 37:17.133
Yes, ma'am.

37:17.133 --> 37:19.667
I'm sorry, my husband's
a little nuts.

37:19.667 --> 37:22.734
This is Decca Records.
What?

37:22.734 --> 37:24.867
(continues indistinctly)

37:24.867 --> 37:27.100
Whoo! Charlie,
that's Decca Records.

37:27.100 --> 37:30.333
"Walkin' after Midnight"
jumped all the way to number 16!

37:30.333 --> 37:32.500
I am on the son of
a bitchin' charts!

37:32.500 --> 37:34.433
Yahoo!

37:34.433 --> 37:36.600
Goddamn it, baby!

37:36.600 --> 37:38.667
Let's go spend some money.
Yeah.

37:38.667 --> 37:41.100
(both)
Mwah, mwah.

37:41.100 --> 37:42.533
(both laughing)

37:42.533 --> 37:44.934
♪ I heard him singing ♪

37:44.934 --> 37:48.567
♪ A most peculiar
cowboy song... ♪

37:48.567 --> 37:52.266
I got a letter
from Washington.

37:52.266 --> 37:54.200
Probably from that
fool Eisenhower,

37:54.200 --> 37:55.567
wanting to know why
I didn't vote for him.

37:55.567 --> 37:59.166
♪ Comma ti yippity yi yeah
get along... ♪

37:59.166 --> 38:02.633
Shit me,
I've been drafted.

38:02.633 --> 38:03.934
What?

38:03.934 --> 38:06.066
They want me to
show up next week.

38:06.066 --> 38:07.400
I can't be drafted.

38:07.400 --> 38:09.767
I'm in the friggin'
National Guard.

38:09.767 --> 38:13.133
Charlie, you said they never
miss you at those meetings.

38:13.133 --> 38:16.367
Yeah, well, I ain't goin',
I'll tell you that much.

38:16.367 --> 38:18.934
I'll shoot my toe off.

38:18.934 --> 38:20.834
I'll tell 'em
I'm a homo! I will!

38:20.834 --> 38:23.000
I ain't goin'!

38:23.000 --> 38:25.500
(crying)
I love you.

38:25.500 --> 38:27.767
Take care of yourself, okay?

38:27.767 --> 38:29.433
Bye, baby!

38:29.433 --> 38:31.800
Charlie!
(crying)

38:31.800 --> 38:36.033
Well, now, it ain't
the end of the world.

38:37.734 --> 38:41.533
Fort Bragg's not exactly
a million miles away.

38:41.533 --> 38:43.567
And you got that
tour coming up.

38:43.567 --> 38:45.333
Oh, shit! Why don't
you just tell me

38:45.333 --> 38:48.333
every cloud's got
a silver linin'?

38:48.333 --> 38:51.567
Why don't you just come on
and move in with me, honey?

38:51.567 --> 38:55.000
No sense in paying
rent on your place.

38:57.834 --> 39:02.900
♪ Shall I stay... ♪

39:02.900 --> 39:04.433
Well, good mornin'.

39:04.433 --> 39:06.000
♪ Would it be... ♪

39:06.000 --> 39:07.900
Says who?

39:07.900 --> 39:09.567
Oh, for heaven's sake, girl.

39:09.567 --> 39:11.934
Sit up and take some
nourishment.

39:11.934 --> 39:14.300
Charlie'll have his first
leave in three weeks,

39:14.300 --> 39:17.600
and you walk around with your
lower lip draggin' the floor.

39:17.600 --> 39:19.200
Big bawlin' baby.

39:19.200 --> 39:22.000
I oughta just fix you
a sugar tit.

39:23.934 --> 39:25.567
You know, you're still
not too big for me

39:25.567 --> 39:27.700
to smack your jaws
for you, you know that?

39:27.700 --> 39:29.233
You make that sign
to me again,

39:29.233 --> 39:31.367
I'll leave the print of
my hand across your face.

39:31.367 --> 39:33.834
I'll make your teeth rattle!

39:36.266 --> 39:38.166
Radio announcer:
For those of you who've
got to get to work,

39:38.166 --> 39:39.734
it's 8:30 in the morning.

39:39.734 --> 39:43.066
Let's continue listening
to everybody's favorites.

39:43.066 --> 39:45.600
♪ Take my hand ♪

39:45.600 --> 39:47.767
I got a check today.

39:47.767 --> 39:51.734
♪ Take my whole
life through... ♪

39:51.734 --> 39:55.000
Well, why don't you just
go out and spend some money?

39:55.000 --> 39:57.200
It'll make you feel better.

39:57.200 --> 39:59.367
Says who?

39:59.367 --> 40:03.533
Well, you're just too
mean to live lately.

40:06.133 --> 40:08.467
(horn honking)

40:20.600 --> 40:23.133
Well, what do you think?

40:23.133 --> 40:25.934
I think it's beautiful.

40:25.934 --> 40:27.967
I think I hate it.

40:27.967 --> 40:30.734
You sour, mean thing.

40:30.734 --> 40:33.700
But I know how to
get sweet again.

40:33.700 --> 40:35.934
("Wabash Cannonball" playing)

41:11.967 --> 41:14.567
I'm lookin' for Charlie
Dick of the 20th Battalion.

41:14.567 --> 41:16.800
Yeah, just go down here
and turn left.

41:19.066 --> 41:21.000
Can you tell me where
"C" Company is?

41:21.000 --> 41:22.467
Yes, ma'am, it's
right over there.

41:22.467 --> 41:23.900
There?

41:23.900 --> 41:26.000
Thank you.
You're welcome.

41:29.367 --> 41:31.100
Charlie!

41:31.100 --> 41:33.400
Oh!

41:33.400 --> 41:34.900
(laughing)

41:34.900 --> 41:36.200
Hey, baby.

41:36.200 --> 41:38.033
How are ya?

41:38.033 --> 41:40.000
(laughing)

41:40.000 --> 41:41.600
Oh, darling, what'd they
do to your hair?

41:41.600 --> 41:42.633
They cut it.

41:42.633 --> 41:44.667
Eat your hearts out!

41:53.800 --> 41:55.867
Whoo!

41:55.867 --> 41:57.667
(laughing)

41:59.867 --> 42:01.066
Come on, honey.

42:01.066 --> 42:02.767
Hurry up,
get the key in there.

42:09.834 --> 42:12.066
I was waitin' to see you.

42:12.066 --> 42:13.633
Mmm...

42:18.934 --> 42:20.400
Wait, Charlie.
What? What?

42:20.400 --> 42:22.567
I gotta close the window.
Hurry up.

42:30.200 --> 42:32.400
You know something, Charlie?

42:32.400 --> 42:34.266
Hmm?

42:36.900 --> 42:40.934
You can't go to your grave
saying you weren't ever loved.

42:42.567 --> 42:44.667
'Cause no matter
what happens to you

42:44.667 --> 42:48.867
for the rest of your life...

42:48.867 --> 42:54.100
Right now, by God,
somebody loves you.

42:55.867 --> 42:57.900
Totally.

42:59.367 --> 43:04.133
♪ I know that you've been
foolin' around on me ♪

43:04.133 --> 43:06.767
♪ Right from the start ♪

43:06.767 --> 43:12.433
♪ So I'll give back your ring
and I'll take back my heart ♪

43:12.433 --> 43:15.066
♪ And when you're tired of
foolin' around ♪

43:15.066 --> 43:17.867
♪ With two or three ♪

43:17.867 --> 43:23.467
♪ Then come on home and fool
around with me ♪

43:23.467 --> 43:25.834
♪ So, honey, fool around ♪

43:25.834 --> 43:28.934
♪ You know right where I'm at ♪

43:28.934 --> 43:31.467
♪ And don't worry if I'm
lonesome ♪

43:31.467 --> 43:34.633
♪ 'Cause I'm used to that ♪

43:34.633 --> 43:37.400
♪ And when you're tired of
foolin' around ♪

43:37.400 --> 43:40.066
♪ With two or three ♪

43:40.066 --> 43:44.834
♪ Then come on home and fool
around with me ♪

43:44.834 --> 43:47.033
♪♪

43:51.066 --> 43:52.900
Hey...

43:52.900 --> 43:55.200
♪ Won't you come home,
Bill Bailey ♪

43:55.200 --> 43:56.900
♪ Won't you come home ♪

43:56.900 --> 44:01.300
♪ I'm home the whole day long ♪

44:01.300 --> 44:03.600
♪ I'll do the cookin', honey ♪

44:03.600 --> 44:05.600
♪ I'll pay the rent ♪

44:05.600 --> 44:08.934
♪ I know I've done you wrong ♪

44:08.934 --> 44:13.367
♪ Remember that rainy
evenin' I drove you out ♪

44:13.367 --> 44:16.467
♪ With nothin' but
a fine tooth comb ♪

44:16.467 --> 44:17.567
Take it home.

44:17.567 --> 44:19.700
♪ I know that I'm to blame ♪

44:19.700 --> 44:21.633
♪ And ain't that a shame ♪

44:21.633 --> 44:24.433
♪ Bill Bailey, won't you
please come home ♪

44:24.433 --> 44:26.066
♪ Come home, Bill Bailey ♪

44:26.066 --> 44:32.233
♪ Bill Bailey, won't you
please come home ♪♪

44:35.033 --> 44:38.834
Lord, I'm give out.

44:38.834 --> 44:42.767
I'm so tired,
my ass is draggin'
the floor behind me.

44:42.767 --> 44:45.266
I'm so tired,
I wished I was dead.

44:47.967 --> 44:51.967
I'm so tired, I wished
I'd never been born.

44:51.967 --> 44:53.367
I'm so tired,
I wished my daddy'd

44:53.367 --> 44:55.467
had his thing cut
off so he'd never...

44:55.467 --> 44:58.834
God Almighty! Will you
boys let it be?

44:58.834 --> 45:03.667
♪ Rollin' in my sweet
baby's arms ♪

45:03.667 --> 45:10.233
♪ Rollin' in
my sweet baby's arms ♪

45:10.233 --> 45:12.800
♪ Gonna lay around this shack ♪

45:12.800 --> 45:16.000
♪ Till the milk train
comes back ♪

45:16.000 --> 45:21.200
♪ Rollin' in my sweet
baby's arms ♪

45:21.200 --> 45:27.333
♪ I ain't gonna work
on the railroad ♪

45:27.333 --> 45:31.467
♪ I ain't gonna
work on the farm ♪

45:31.467 --> 45:34.367
♪ Gonna lay around this shack ♪

45:34.367 --> 45:36.934
♪ Till the milk train
comes back ♪

45:36.934 --> 45:42.400
♪ Rollin' in
my sweet baby's arms ♪

45:42.400 --> 45:47.233
♪ Rollin' in my sweet
baby's arms ♪

45:47.233 --> 45:51.100
♪ Rollin' in
my sweet baby's arms ♪

45:51.100 --> 45:53.734
♪ Gonna lay around this shack ♪

45:53.734 --> 45:56.000
♪ Till the milk train
comes back ♪

45:56.000 --> 46:00.767
♪ Rollin' in my sweet
baby's arms ♪

46:04.967 --> 46:07.500
(retching)

46:09.300 --> 46:10.900
(knock on door)
Patsy?

46:10.900 --> 46:13.066
Patsy, are you okay?

46:13.066 --> 46:15.600
(sighs)

46:15.600 --> 46:17.767
Ohh...

46:17.767 --> 46:20.200
Darling, tell those boys
they'll have to wait.

46:20.200 --> 46:21.834
I can't get up.

46:21.834 --> 46:23.800
Okay.

46:23.800 --> 46:25.834
(indistinct chatter)

46:31.767 --> 46:33.934
How about it, honey,
you gonna live?

46:33.934 --> 46:36.000
Oh, Lord,
I've been better.

46:37.834 --> 46:40.767
Let me have a sip of this.

46:49.333 --> 46:51.000
Do you have to do that
in the mornin'?

46:51.000 --> 46:52.333
It puts hair
on your head.

46:55.367 --> 46:57.433
Oh, my God in heaven!

46:57.433 --> 47:00.300
I bet I'm pregnant.

47:00.300 --> 47:03.433
Lord, I can't be pregnant.

47:03.433 --> 47:05.400
I mean, I just
had a hit record.

47:05.400 --> 47:07.567
My husband's in the army.

47:07.567 --> 47:10.500
(laughing)
I mean, oh, Lord.

47:10.500 --> 47:13.400
How the hell am I gonna
tour if I'm pregnant?

47:13.400 --> 47:18.834
Oh, God, you talk
about your bad timin'.

47:22.367 --> 47:24.867
Please, Fred,
don't eat that.

47:27.700 --> 47:30.734
(children playing,
dog barks)

47:34.900 --> 47:37.000
(barking continues)

47:40.934 --> 47:43.266
♪ Bye-bye, baby, goodbye ♪

47:44.867 --> 47:46.867
♪ I saw my baby... ♪

47:46.867 --> 47:48.800
Hi, honey.

47:48.800 --> 47:51.500
Charlie...

47:51.500 --> 47:53.433
Look at me, honey.

47:55.400 --> 47:57.300
You think I look just awful?

47:57.300 --> 48:01.233
Hell, no, you look
great, baby.

48:01.233 --> 48:03.467
You always do.

48:04.934 --> 48:06.333
Thanks.

48:06.333 --> 48:07.967
♪ My baby said
goodbye to me ♪

48:07.967 --> 48:10.433
♪ Bye-bye, baby, goodbye ♪

48:20.667 --> 48:22.667
Charlie?
Mm-hmm?

48:22.667 --> 48:25.567
I'm crazy 'bout you, baby.

48:25.567 --> 48:26.800
I love you all the time.

48:29.734 --> 48:31.867
Come here, come here.

48:31.867 --> 48:33.300
You sure you want to?

48:35.033 --> 48:36.433
Whoo!

48:36.433 --> 48:39.300
Look out, look out,
I'm comin' to get you.

48:39.300 --> 48:41.000
(laughing)
Look out, I got you.

48:41.000 --> 48:42.333
Ahh!

48:42.333 --> 48:44.633
I'm coming to get! Ahh!

48:44.633 --> 48:47.066
Okay, I'm coming to get you.

48:48.834 --> 48:50.266
Ah, baby.

48:53.000 --> 48:56.100
You still like me, Charlie?

48:56.100 --> 48:57.467
Yeah.

48:57.467 --> 48:59.066
You do?

48:59.066 --> 49:00.367
Yeah.

49:04.800 --> 49:07.166
Mmm...

49:07.166 --> 49:13.233
♪ When we met I believed
the words you told me ♪

49:15.300 --> 49:21.500
♪ How was I to know
you'd be untrue ♪

49:21.500 --> 49:25.467
Lord, bitch, you don't sing.
You whine, you whine.

49:27.233 --> 49:29.400
Hi, darlin'.

49:31.000 --> 49:33.133
What are you doin'?

49:33.133 --> 49:36.200
Havin' a glass of champagne
with Kirk Douglas.

49:36.200 --> 49:38.266
What's it look
like I'm doin'?

49:38.266 --> 49:40.767
You don't have to iron
me a shirt every day, you know.

49:40.767 --> 49:43.500
I thought you told me Sergeant
Wilson wanted you lookin' sharp.

49:43.500 --> 49:45.533
Hey, I'll tell you a secret.

49:45.533 --> 49:48.000
I don't give a good goddamn
what Sergeant Wilson says.

49:48.000 --> 49:49.767
That tight-assed bastard's
been on my back

49:49.767 --> 49:52.000
ever since I got here.

49:54.667 --> 49:57.200
God, I hate this army.

49:57.200 --> 49:58.633
I hate this state.

49:58.633 --> 50:00.734
And I hate this stinking
little miserable apartment.

50:00.734 --> 50:03.700
Well, I've been places
I like better, too.

50:03.700 --> 50:06.433
I could still be making
records if I'd stayed home.

50:06.433 --> 50:08.633
Nobody asked you
to come here!

50:08.633 --> 50:10.400
(chuckling)
The hell you didn't!

50:10.400 --> 50:11.734
You begged me!

50:11.734 --> 50:12.767
Yeah, well, I didn't mean it.

50:12.767 --> 50:16.166
Oh, come on, Charlie,
don't fuss now.

50:16.166 --> 50:18.533
I'm makin' chili for dinner,
you like that.

50:18.533 --> 50:20.400
Let's just be nice!

50:20.400 --> 50:21.934
(mocking)
Oh, my...

50:21.934 --> 50:24.800
"I'm makin' chili,
and I try to be nice,

50:24.800 --> 50:27.033
but my husband's just
so rude and nasty."

50:27.033 --> 50:28.033
Oh, shut up.

50:28.033 --> 50:29.667
Oh, poor Patsy!

50:29.667 --> 50:31.133
Why don't you just
shut your mouth?

50:31.133 --> 50:32.533
Why don't you just
try and make me?

50:32.533 --> 50:34.033
Don't push me, Charlie.

50:34.033 --> 50:35.567
I dare you.

50:39.900 --> 50:42.900
Uhh!

50:42.900 --> 50:43.900
Patsy...

50:43.900 --> 50:45.133
Patsy!

50:45.133 --> 50:46.700
Leave me alone!

50:48.600 --> 50:51.600
You know the part I remember?

50:51.600 --> 50:54.266
I remember the part when
you told me over and over

50:54.266 --> 50:56.233
how you're gonna protect me.

50:56.233 --> 50:59.233
Keep anybody from hurtin' me!

50:59.233 --> 51:01.500
You remember all those
times you told me that?!

51:01.500 --> 51:02.734
Patsy, wait!

51:02.734 --> 51:03.867
(Patsy screams,
slams door)

51:03.867 --> 51:06.367
(lock clicks)
Patsy, I'm sorry.

51:06.367 --> 51:09.233
(rattles doorknob)
Come on, open the door up.

51:15.467 --> 51:18.467
I'll bring the rest.

51:18.467 --> 51:20.667
(Patsy)
Will you get the
baby things, John?

51:20.667 --> 51:22.734
Okay, sis.

51:32.633 --> 51:34.400
("Walkin' After Midnight"
playing on record player)

51:34.400 --> 51:36.934
I'm gonna start singin' again
right after the baby's born.

51:36.934 --> 51:39.767
Hilda:
Oh, I was hopin' you'd
stay home for a while.

51:39.767 --> 51:44.266
I'm gonna start singin' the
same week the baby's born.

51:44.266 --> 51:46.934
I can make it, Mama,
damn it, I know I can.

51:46.934 --> 51:48.734
All I need is just
one good song,

51:48.734 --> 51:51.333
one good song to put me
over the top.

51:51.333 --> 51:55.266
Then when I've made enough,
I can retire, raise the baby.

51:55.266 --> 51:57.300
♪ I walk for miles... ♪

51:57.300 --> 51:59.767
I just wanna
make it right.

51:59.767 --> 52:02.500
You forgot the part
about the yellow roses.

52:08.367 --> 52:10.734
(distant train whistle)

52:18.333 --> 52:19.600
Hmm...

52:23.333 --> 52:24.934
Ahh...

52:35.867 --> 52:38.166
(horn honking)

52:49.700 --> 52:52.100
(music playing)

52:55.500 --> 52:57.133
What the livin' hell?
They told me you were--

52:57.133 --> 52:59.066
It's a false alarm.

53:01.867 --> 53:03.633
Hilda, why don't you
put a star in your crown,

53:03.633 --> 53:06.333
and go get old
Charlie a beer?

53:06.333 --> 53:08.266
(music stops)

53:12.266 --> 53:13.433
Can I have a kiss?

53:18.667 --> 53:21.166
Can I have a decent kiss?

53:28.233 --> 53:30.633
Miss me?

53:30.633 --> 53:32.600
Nope.

53:37.500 --> 53:41.667
I didn't know it till
I saw you, but, yes, I did.

53:43.166 --> 53:44.767
Look at you.

53:46.033 --> 53:49.100
I got ten days' leave.

53:49.100 --> 53:52.166
I got two good-lookin'
women to spend it with...

53:52.166 --> 53:53.900
and a baby on the way!

53:53.900 --> 53:56.200
(laughing)

53:56.200 --> 53:58.333
Hog heaven!

54:02.166 --> 54:04.166
Mmm...

54:05.767 --> 54:09.166
(Patsy)
Mama, look at these sweet little
things Betty just gave me.

54:09.166 --> 54:10.533
Oh, they...
Aren't they darlin'?

54:10.533 --> 54:11.867
Look at that one.

54:11.867 --> 54:13.867
It's got a little
bit of embroidery.

54:13.867 --> 54:15.667
(football game plays)

54:17.633 --> 54:20.000
Damn it! Get your feet
off the baby's clothes.

54:20.000 --> 54:21.300
Aah!

54:21.300 --> 54:24.000
Charlie, for the love of God!

54:24.000 --> 54:26.400
Why don't you get out
from under our feet?

54:26.400 --> 54:29.800
Go buy yourself a beer
or something, Lord.

54:31.166 --> 54:33.100
All right, if that's what
you think I should do.

54:33.100 --> 54:35.200
Yeah.

54:35.200 --> 54:37.533
Dinner's at 6:00!
All right.

54:37.533 --> 54:39.400
Charlie here says
he loves the army.

54:39.400 --> 54:40.834
Oh, hell, yes.

54:40.834 --> 54:42.700
Says he's gonna re-enlist
when his time's up.

54:42.700 --> 54:44.000
(chuckling)

54:44.000 --> 54:45.200
You know, Woodhouse,

54:45.200 --> 54:47.200
I never saw so many
teeth in a horse's ass.

54:47.200 --> 54:48.500
(laughing)

54:48.500 --> 54:49.667
I gotta go.

54:49.667 --> 54:51.266
Oh, you butthole,
come on.

54:51.266 --> 54:53.000
I didn't know they made
apron strings this long.

54:53.000 --> 54:54.333
I gotta get home.

54:54.333 --> 54:56.000
Come on, let's stop
and have one.
I gotta get home.

54:56.000 --> 54:57.233
It's on the way,
just a quick one.

54:57.233 --> 54:59.467
(chatter and laughter)

55:00.667 --> 55:03.600
Hey, bartender, let us
have a shot for everybody.

55:03.600 --> 55:05.467
No, not for me.

55:05.467 --> 55:07.333
Nothing but the best for
Charlie.

55:07.333 --> 55:09.667
Woman:
Yes, one more, just
for you one now.

55:09.667 --> 55:11.333
One more.
Just one before you go.

55:11.333 --> 55:12.800
No, I gotta get goin'.

55:12.800 --> 55:14.400
You all... y'all
have a good night.

55:14.400 --> 55:16.400
It's been real nice.
I'll see you before I go.

55:16.400 --> 55:17.734
All right.
Hey, Charlie.

55:17.734 --> 55:19.000
What?

55:19.000 --> 55:20.533
Oh, nothin'.
What?

55:20.533 --> 55:23.266
(chuckling)
Well, your hair is all...

55:23.266 --> 55:25.633
You look so different
with short hair.

55:25.633 --> 55:26.767
So?

55:26.767 --> 55:29.667
So, I think
it's kind of cute.

55:29.667 --> 55:31.633
I like it.

55:32.800 --> 55:34.567
(chuckling)

55:34.567 --> 55:36.467
Remember? Hmm?

55:36.467 --> 55:39.333
All those good times we had.

55:39.333 --> 55:40.567
(laughing)

55:40.567 --> 55:42.233
Yeah, I remember.

55:42.233 --> 55:44.266
(sighs)
Of course, I remember.

55:44.266 --> 55:48.533
Well, why do you have
to go home so early, then?

55:50.867 --> 55:52.834
Talk to me, Charlie.

55:57.800 --> 56:00.367
You know I've always
liked you, Charlie.

56:03.066 --> 56:04.867
We're goin'
to Carol's house.

56:04.867 --> 56:06.700
Come on, Charlie.

56:10.066 --> 56:12.066
Let's get outta here.

56:14.633 --> 56:16.300
Is the father around
so I can get

56:16.300 --> 56:18.467
the rest of this
information from him?

56:18.467 --> 56:20.200
Well, what's his name?

56:20.200 --> 56:22.166
Charles Dick.

56:22.166 --> 56:23.900
Son of a bitch!

56:23.900 --> 56:25.767
Stop that
dirty talk now.

56:25.767 --> 56:27.967
He'll be here soon.

56:27.967 --> 56:30.734
The son of a bitch!

56:30.734 --> 56:33.000
(laughing)

56:33.000 --> 56:34.800
Oh, Mama...
(laughing)

56:42.400 --> 56:45.000
(phone ringing)

56:47.133 --> 56:48.967
(ringing)

56:50.867 --> 56:53.100
Somebody answer the phone!

56:55.266 --> 56:56.867
(ringing)

56:56.867 --> 56:58.633
Hello.

56:58.633 --> 57:00.033
Hilda: Charlie?

57:00.033 --> 57:01.033
Hilda, where are you?

57:01.033 --> 57:03.100
Charlie, we're
at the hospital.

57:03.100 --> 57:04.400
She's had her baby.

57:04.400 --> 57:05.433
I'll be right down.

57:05.433 --> 57:06.934
No, you won't be right down.

57:06.934 --> 57:09.200
You just keep
your miserable self away.

57:09.200 --> 57:11.667
She had a hard time
and she's finally asleep.

57:11.667 --> 57:15.934
She asked for you 14 times
tonight, and you weren't there.

57:15.934 --> 57:19.600
Damn your soul,
Charlie Dick, where were you?

57:49.900 --> 57:52.166
There's your dad.

57:55.467 --> 57:57.266
Hi, honey.

58:01.400 --> 58:03.266
She's beautiful.

58:06.333 --> 58:08.300
You want to hold her?

58:08.300 --> 58:10.300
Yeah....

58:10.300 --> 58:12.200
(baby coos)

58:12.200 --> 58:15.066
Come here,
you little thing.

58:15.066 --> 58:16.533
(chuckling)

58:16.533 --> 58:18.133
I got her.

58:18.133 --> 58:20.066
I got ya.

58:21.567 --> 58:24.700
Woman over PA:
Dr. Hollis, first floor
at 3:00, please.

58:24.700 --> 58:28.500
Dr. Hollis, please come
to first floor at 3:00.

58:28.500 --> 58:29.700
She's so pretty.

58:29.700 --> 58:30.967
Yeah.

58:30.967 --> 58:32.533
Look at her hair.
I know.

58:32.533 --> 58:34.767
It's curlin' already.

58:38.900 --> 58:41.867
You still think Julie's
a good name for her?

58:49.500 --> 58:51.700
I wish to God
I'd been with you.

58:51.700 --> 58:54.233
Yeah, where were you?

58:54.233 --> 58:57.967
I'd tell you a hundred
lies, but I ain't goin' to.

58:57.967 --> 58:59.600
Got drunk.

59:02.367 --> 59:05.500
(chuckling)

59:05.500 --> 59:08.567
That's whiskey
under the bridge.

59:38.867 --> 59:40.667
(coin clinks)

59:48.567 --> 59:50.300
(line ringing)

59:50.300 --> 59:51.667
Operator:
50 cents, please.

59:51.667 --> 59:53.100
Yes, ma'am.

59:55.066 --> 59:57.467
(line ringing)

59:57.467 --> 59:59.133
Patsy: Hello?
Hi, baby, it's me.

59:59.133 --> 01:00:00.266
Hi, Charlie.

01:00:00.266 --> 01:00:01.767
Guess what?
What?

01:00:01.767 --> 01:00:03.533
I found us a new apartment.

01:00:03.533 --> 01:00:05.533
It's got room for the baby,
and it's still cheaper

01:00:05.533 --> 01:00:07.834
than that other one
we had down here.

01:00:07.834 --> 01:00:10.934
Got a big kitchen, too.

01:00:10.934 --> 01:00:13.567
So, what do you say?
Why don't you come on down?

01:00:13.567 --> 01:00:15.700
No, Charlie, I can't.

01:00:15.700 --> 01:00:19.033
I want to start singin' again,
and Mama helps me with Julie.

01:00:19.033 --> 01:00:21.133
Come on, baby.

01:00:21.133 --> 01:00:23.433
I really miss ya.
I wanna see my kid.

01:00:23.433 --> 01:00:25.600
Well, don't you get another
leave in a couple of months?

01:00:25.600 --> 01:00:27.300
You can certainly
see her then.

01:00:27.300 --> 01:00:29.600
Goddamn, why are you
so polite anymore?

01:00:29.600 --> 01:00:31.100
Can't you just talk normal?

01:00:31.100 --> 01:00:33.600
I feel like I'm talkin'
to Eleanor Roosevelt.

01:00:33.600 --> 01:00:36.166
I gotta go, Charlie,
the baby's cryin'.

01:00:36.166 --> 01:00:37.700
I'll talk to you, okay?

01:00:37.700 --> 01:00:39.767
Yeah, okay,
if Julie's cryin'.

01:00:39.767 --> 01:00:41.667
(dial tone)

01:01:49.033 --> 01:01:51.233
Charlie:
Patsy.

01:01:51.233 --> 01:01:53.166
You awake?

01:01:53.166 --> 01:01:54.700
Come on, wake up, baby.

01:01:54.700 --> 01:01:56.133
Patsy?
(gasps)

01:01:56.133 --> 01:01:57.367
Shh.

01:01:57.367 --> 01:01:59.166
Put something on.
I wanna take you someplace.

01:01:59.166 --> 01:02:00.700
What's the matter?
What are you doing here?

01:02:00.700 --> 01:02:02.266
Come on,
come on, it's important.

01:02:02.266 --> 01:02:04.133
What are you crazy?
It's the middle of night!

01:02:04.133 --> 01:02:06.066
Come on, come on.
I can't leave the baby.

01:02:06.066 --> 01:02:07.533
We'll put her in
with Hilda, come on.

01:02:22.533 --> 01:02:25.200
Charlie, why won't you tell me
what this is all about?

01:02:25.200 --> 01:02:28.100
Just wait.

01:02:28.100 --> 01:02:31.066
Well, at least tell me
where we're going.

01:02:31.066 --> 01:02:32.834
Shh...

01:02:42.834 --> 01:02:45.233
("Stranger on the Shore"
playing)

01:03:10.767 --> 01:03:12.934
I need something
from you.

01:03:14.700 --> 01:03:16.867
I need you to look me
in the face and say,

01:03:16.867 --> 01:03:19.467
"You screw up a lot, but
I still love you, Charlie.

01:03:19.467 --> 01:03:21.734
And I always will."

01:03:21.734 --> 01:03:25.400
I told you before you left,
I'm not holding any grudges.

01:03:26.700 --> 01:03:30.100
I need something from you.

01:03:30.100 --> 01:03:32.400
I need you to look me
in the face and say,

01:03:32.400 --> 01:03:33.700
"You screw up a lot,

01:03:33.700 --> 01:03:36.200
but I still love you,
Charlie, I always will."

01:03:46.467 --> 01:03:49.133
You screw up a lot, Charlie.

01:03:49.133 --> 01:03:51.633
But I still love
you and I always will.

01:03:51.633 --> 01:03:53.800
Say it again.

01:03:53.800 --> 01:03:56.266
You screw up a lot,

01:03:56.266 --> 01:04:00.333
but I still love you, Charlie,
I always will.

01:04:18.066 --> 01:04:23.467
♪ I'll have a blue Christmas ♪

01:04:23.467 --> 01:04:26.433
♪ Without you ♪

01:04:26.433 --> 01:04:29.767
♪ I'll be so blue ♪

01:04:29.767 --> 01:04:35.367
♪ Thinking about you ♪

01:04:35.367 --> 01:04:39.967
♪ Decorations of red ♪

01:04:39.967 --> 01:04:43.567
♪ On a green Christmas tree ♪

01:04:43.567 --> 01:04:45.433
Man: Start the movie!

01:04:45.433 --> 01:04:49.934
♪ Won't mean
a thing, dear, if... ♪

01:04:49.934 --> 01:04:51.333
(music continues)

01:04:51.333 --> 01:04:52.900
What are they doin'?

01:04:52.900 --> 01:04:55.200
What the hell's goin' on?

01:04:55.200 --> 01:04:58.133
Woody Woodpecker:
Guess who!

01:05:00.734 --> 01:05:02.633
Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!
Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:05:02.633 --> 01:05:04.033
Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:05:04.033 --> 01:05:06.700
(Woody laughing)

01:05:06.700 --> 01:05:08.734
(music from cartoon continues)

01:05:08.734 --> 01:05:11.700
I cannot believe this!

01:05:13.300 --> 01:05:15.266
Ugh!
Shh.

01:05:15.266 --> 01:05:18.000
Oh, honey, your mama's
life is not workin' out.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:21.300
Trust me,
it's not working out!

01:05:21.300 --> 01:05:22.500
(car starts)

01:05:22.500 --> 01:05:24.667
I'm goin' down to
Nashville tomorrow, Mama.

01:05:24.667 --> 01:05:27.900
See if I can do something.

01:05:52.133 --> 01:05:54.066
Hey, aren't you Patsy Cline?

01:05:54.066 --> 01:05:55.600
Yeah?

01:05:55.600 --> 01:05:56.867
I'm Randy Hughes.

01:05:56.867 --> 01:05:58.834
Hey, I was just
coming to see you.

01:05:58.834 --> 01:06:00.333
Is that right?
Yeah.

01:06:00.333 --> 01:06:02.767
You know, you wrote me a letter
about a year ago or so, but...

01:06:02.767 --> 01:06:04.533
Mm-hmm.
I had a baby since then.

01:06:04.533 --> 01:06:06.633
I haven't been doin'
too much singing but I--

01:06:06.633 --> 01:06:08.333
You don't have to sell me.

01:06:08.333 --> 01:06:09.934
I happen to think
you're maybe

01:06:09.934 --> 01:06:11.767
the best country
singer in the world.

01:06:11.767 --> 01:06:14.166
(chuckling)
Come in here.

01:06:14.166 --> 01:06:15.333
Let's you and I talk.

01:06:15.333 --> 01:06:17.033
I always did like
a man who knew

01:06:17.033 --> 01:06:19.967
how to start off
a conversation good.

01:06:19.967 --> 01:06:23.767
I swear, I can make us
both a lot of money.

01:06:23.767 --> 01:06:26.133
You won't be sorry.
You know why not?

01:06:26.133 --> 01:06:27.400
Why?

01:06:27.400 --> 01:06:30.433
Because when the song
is right and I feel it,

01:06:30.433 --> 01:06:32.700
I can tell from looking
at people's faces

01:06:32.700 --> 01:06:35.033
that I've reached right down
there inside them.

01:06:35.033 --> 01:06:37.500
You got any idea
what that feels like?

01:06:37.500 --> 01:06:39.500
You wanna be
Kitty Wells, right?

01:06:39.500 --> 01:06:42.333
Hell, no!
I wanna be Hank Williams!

01:06:42.333 --> 01:06:43.867
All right.

01:06:43.867 --> 01:06:47.266
Sit down, listen to me.

01:06:47.266 --> 01:06:50.200
I got a story to tell you.

01:06:51.734 --> 01:06:55.066
I heard you sing one night
in a dump in Virginia.

01:06:55.066 --> 01:06:57.834
12 tables,
watered-down drinks.

01:06:57.834 --> 01:07:00.333
Dance floor the size
of that coffee table.

01:07:00.333 --> 01:07:02.567
And you were good.

01:07:02.567 --> 01:07:04.066
The crowd liked ya.

01:07:04.066 --> 01:07:07.100
Just ate up all that yodelin'
and growlin' stuff.

01:07:07.100 --> 01:07:12.533
And then you let go on
"Walkin' the Floor Over You."

01:07:12.533 --> 01:07:17.033
But you did it slow,
like a ballad.

01:07:17.033 --> 01:07:19.400
And I'm tellin' you,

01:07:19.400 --> 01:07:22.667
the hair on the back
of my neck stood up.

01:07:22.667 --> 01:07:26.900
I mean, there I was
in this dive in Virginia,

01:07:26.900 --> 01:07:30.600
and I was listening to
something real special.

01:07:30.600 --> 01:07:31.967
Yeah.

01:07:31.967 --> 01:07:33.600
You get my drift?

01:07:33.600 --> 01:07:34.600
Nope.

01:07:34.600 --> 01:07:37.100
I'll make it simple.

01:07:37.100 --> 01:07:43.700
You got a voice that was
made to sing love songs.

01:07:43.700 --> 01:07:46.300
And if I work with you,

01:07:46.300 --> 01:07:48.467
we take advantage
of that fact.

01:07:51.100 --> 01:07:52.633
Patsy:
I don't wanna talk
about it anymore.

01:07:52.633 --> 01:07:55.200
I got a couple starving kids
waiting for me in the car.

01:07:55.200 --> 01:07:57.100
Randy:
It's too late, Patsy,
it's all set up.

01:07:57.100 --> 01:07:58.734
I don't give a damn!

01:07:58.734 --> 01:08:01.900
I don't want four big male
singers drowning me out.

01:08:01.900 --> 01:08:03.100
Well, they've been booked

01:08:03.100 --> 01:08:04.400
and they're gonna
be there at 2:00.

01:08:04.400 --> 01:08:06.800
Yeah, well, if they're there,
I'm not showing up.

01:08:06.800 --> 01:08:08.200
Musicians are booked.

01:08:08.200 --> 01:08:09.567
Owen Bradley's
gonna be there.

01:08:09.567 --> 01:08:10.800
I'm gonna be there.

01:08:10.800 --> 01:08:12.200
You can show up or not.

01:08:12.200 --> 01:08:13.567
Just suit your damn self.

01:08:13.567 --> 01:08:14.700
I will.

01:08:14.700 --> 01:08:16.433
2:00.

01:08:16.433 --> 01:08:19.800
Grab hold of Randy, Madrine.

01:08:19.800 --> 01:08:23.466
They got four singers
backing me up today, big ones.

01:08:23.466 --> 01:08:25.466
They're just gonna
drown me out.

01:08:25.466 --> 01:08:27.466
Hell's bells!

01:08:27.466 --> 01:08:30.100
All right, now let's
have the next bit.

01:08:30.100 --> 01:08:31.600
One, two.

01:08:31.600 --> 01:08:33.200
♪ Ooh... ♪

01:08:37.734 --> 01:08:40.700
(vocalizing continues)

01:08:40.700 --> 01:08:42.133
Hello there.

01:08:42.133 --> 01:08:43.567
Did you tell
'em what I said?

01:08:43.567 --> 01:08:45.700
Mr. Bradley is the
producer, darling.

01:08:47.233 --> 01:08:49.533
Hello, Patsy.
Hi, Mr. Bradley.

01:08:49.533 --> 01:08:51.066
What's the frown for, honey?

01:08:51.066 --> 01:08:52.600
Randy's tellin' me you've
been worryin' again.

01:08:52.600 --> 01:08:53.800
Don't ever frown.

01:08:53.800 --> 01:08:55.233
You'll make yourself old
before your time.

01:08:55.233 --> 01:08:56.966
I know, but I wanted to talk to
you about something--

01:08:56.966 --> 01:08:58.133
No, now listen to me.
Everything's all right.

01:08:58.133 --> 01:08:59.500
The song's a good one.

01:08:59.500 --> 01:09:00.734
The arrangement's
a good one.

01:09:00.734 --> 01:09:01.966
The backup singers are good.

01:09:01.966 --> 01:09:03.367
Even the glazed
doughnuts are good.

01:09:03.367 --> 01:09:07.133
Everything's good today,
so relax and be happy and sing!

01:09:09.265 --> 01:09:11.200
Well, just make
sure they hear me.

01:09:11.200 --> 01:09:13.533
Sing!
Sing!

01:09:13.533 --> 01:09:15.300
Man:
Take seven coming up.

01:09:15.300 --> 01:09:18.233
(Intro to "I Fall to Pieces"
begins)

01:09:23.899 --> 01:09:26.265
"I Fall to Pieces"
intro playing)

01:09:26.265 --> 01:09:28.567
(cheering and applause)

01:09:30.233 --> 01:09:33.033
All right, I can see
you all recognize that song.

01:09:33.033 --> 01:09:35.265
Well, that's just great because
we just happen to have

01:09:35.265 --> 01:09:37.633
a little girl backstage
that made that famous

01:09:37.633 --> 01:09:39.500
with her number one
hit record of it.

01:09:39.500 --> 01:09:41.767
We're real proud of her
here at the Grand Old Opry.

01:09:41.767 --> 01:09:44.899
Here's Miss Patsy Cline!

01:09:44.899 --> 01:09:47.000
(cheering and applause)

01:09:51.166 --> 01:09:55.567
♪ I fall ♪

01:09:55.567 --> 01:09:58.834
♪ To pieces ♪

01:09:58.834 --> 01:10:00.800
(cheering and applause)

01:10:00.800 --> 01:10:07.500
♪ Each time I see you again ♪

01:10:08.967 --> 01:10:12.934
♪ I fall ♪

01:10:12.934 --> 01:10:16.433
♪ To pieces ♪

01:10:16.433 --> 01:10:18.266
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

01:10:18.266 --> 01:10:24.800
♪ How can I be just
your friend ♪

01:10:24.800 --> 01:10:29.367
♪ You want me to act ♪

01:10:29.367 --> 01:10:33.500
♪ Like we've never kissed ♪

01:10:33.500 --> 01:10:37.767
♪ You want me to forget ♪

01:10:37.767 --> 01:10:41.934
♪ Pretend we've never met ♪

01:10:41.934 --> 01:10:44.467
♪ And I've tried ♪

01:10:44.467 --> 01:10:47.200
♪ And I've tried ♪

01:10:47.200 --> 01:10:50.967
♪ But I haven't yet ♪

01:10:50.967 --> 01:10:53.700
♪ You walk by ♪

01:10:53.700 --> 01:10:59.400
♪ And I fall to pieces ♪

01:10:59.400 --> 01:11:03.934
♪ You walk by and I ♪

01:11:03.934 --> 01:11:08.767
♪ Fall to pieces ♪♪

01:11:08.767 --> 01:11:11.333
(cheering and applause)

01:11:11.333 --> 01:11:13.533
Thank you!

01:11:15.266 --> 01:11:17.000
(chuckling)

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:18.734
I like everything
you sing, I mean...

01:11:18.734 --> 01:11:21.800
You just open your
mouth and I fall down.

01:11:21.800 --> 01:11:24.567
But when you sing
them slow ones...

01:11:24.567 --> 01:11:27.333
I just love it.

01:11:27.333 --> 01:11:31.033
You know, Randy told me it's
number nine on the pop charts.

01:11:31.033 --> 01:11:32.567
I'm a crossover.

01:11:32.567 --> 01:11:35.533
Money, money, money!
(chuckling)

01:11:35.533 --> 01:11:38.900
I wanna buy Mama
a pure silk dress.

01:11:38.900 --> 01:11:43.567
Give Sylvia that graduation
party she never had.

01:11:43.567 --> 01:11:46.066
I want to spend
some of that money.

01:11:46.066 --> 01:11:47.533
Well, I'll tell you what.

01:11:47.533 --> 01:11:49.633
I'll help you do it.
Yeah?

01:11:51.233 --> 01:11:52.900
(door shuts)

01:11:52.900 --> 01:11:54.200
Charlie:
I'm home, baby!

01:11:54.200 --> 01:11:56.033
Had to crawl part way,
but I made it.

01:11:56.033 --> 01:11:59.033
Ooh, that's pretty.

01:11:59.033 --> 01:12:01.266
Bake that all
by your lonesome?

01:12:01.266 --> 01:12:03.033
I sure did.

01:12:05.934 --> 01:12:09.467
How come you didn't bake
me a cake for my birthday?

01:12:09.467 --> 01:12:11.734
Goddamn it, Charlie,
that's not funny.

01:12:11.734 --> 01:12:14.533
Been working on that all day.

01:12:16.300 --> 01:12:18.333
Oh, look, didn't
this pie turn out nice?

01:12:18.333 --> 01:12:19.433
Mm-hmm.

01:12:19.433 --> 01:12:22.667
Thickened it with tapioca
just like Mama does.

01:12:22.667 --> 01:12:26.266
I can't wait to see her and
John and Sylvie tomorrow.

01:12:27.700 --> 01:12:29.100
Hey, Charlie...

01:12:31.233 --> 01:12:32.467
Hmm?

01:12:32.467 --> 01:12:33.967
Why don't you go
a little easy

01:12:33.967 --> 01:12:36.834
on that drinkin'
tomorrow at the party?

01:12:36.834 --> 01:12:39.500
Why don't you
kiss my furry butt?

01:12:39.500 --> 01:12:42.200
(chuckling)
Well, you think I wouldn't?

01:12:47.600 --> 01:12:50.133
Come on, Charlie, gosh.
Charlie...

01:12:50.133 --> 01:12:52.000
I'm cooking chicken,
come on.

01:12:52.000 --> 01:12:53.133
(chuckling)

01:12:53.133 --> 01:12:54.767
Cookin' chicken, Charlie.
Stop it now.

01:12:54.767 --> 01:12:56.567
Where the kids at?
Everything's gonna burn.

01:12:56.567 --> 01:12:58.000
Hm? Where the kids at?

01:12:58.000 --> 01:12:59.767
They're upstairs
in their bedroom.

01:12:59.767 --> 01:13:00.900
Well, good.
Come on, Charlie...

01:13:00.900 --> 01:13:02.667
Oh, baby.
Oh, Lord!

01:13:02.667 --> 01:13:04.867
On the linoleum floor?

01:13:04.867 --> 01:13:07.467
With my dress
up around my ears?

01:13:07.467 --> 01:13:09.900
Oh, Charlie!

01:13:09.900 --> 01:13:13.100
Try that red hots,
get your red hots here.

01:13:13.100 --> 01:13:15.700
Red hots, red hots.

01:13:15.700 --> 01:13:16.900
Here's a taker for you.

01:13:16.900 --> 01:13:18.600
This just means I spend--
whoa!

01:13:18.600 --> 01:13:20.667
Come on, just like
New York City.

01:13:20.667 --> 01:13:22.767
(chatter, music playing)

01:13:28.233 --> 01:13:31.467
Hey! Hey, everybody,
listen a minute!

01:13:31.467 --> 01:13:33.500
You know that we have
a high school graduate

01:13:33.500 --> 01:13:35.767
in our family
for the very first time!

01:13:35.767 --> 01:13:38.533
And Charlie and I finally
got enough money...

01:13:38.533 --> 01:13:40.667
Finally!

01:13:40.667 --> 01:13:42.500
To give her a party
and buy her a present.

01:13:42.500 --> 01:13:44.734
Here it is!
Happy graduation, Sylvie.

01:13:44.734 --> 01:13:46.734
It's a new toothbrush.

01:13:46.734 --> 01:13:48.166
Whoo!

01:13:50.400 --> 01:13:51.667
(chuckling)

01:13:51.667 --> 01:13:53.600
Don't Sylvia look
sweet today?

01:13:53.600 --> 01:13:54.600
(chuckling)

01:13:54.600 --> 01:13:56.500
Patsy:
I just love her new hairdo.

01:13:56.500 --> 01:13:57.633
(baby crying)

01:13:57.633 --> 01:13:59.300
Mama, I'm gonna put him
down, he's so crabby.

01:13:59.300 --> 01:14:00.333
Oh, good night, honey.

01:14:00.333 --> 01:14:02.066
Give Grandma a kiss.
Nighty-night.

01:14:02.066 --> 01:14:03.867
(crying continues)

01:14:03.867 --> 01:14:05.400
Here, sweetheart.

01:14:05.400 --> 01:14:06.667
Put him down.

01:14:06.667 --> 01:14:08.533
Give Mama a kiss, okay.

01:14:08.533 --> 01:14:10.567
(crying)

01:14:10.567 --> 01:14:11.767
(sighs)

01:14:11.767 --> 01:14:14.533
It just kills me
I don't see him more.

01:14:14.533 --> 01:14:15.900
I know it.

01:14:15.900 --> 01:14:17.100
I wrote that book.

01:14:19.300 --> 01:14:22.033
How's things with
you and Charlie?

01:14:22.033 --> 01:14:24.967
Up and down?

01:14:24.967 --> 01:14:27.300
There's lots
of up and down.

01:14:27.300 --> 01:14:29.734
Oh, Patsy! Ohh...

01:14:29.734 --> 01:14:31.066
Oh!

01:14:31.066 --> 01:14:32.834
(laughing)

01:14:32.834 --> 01:14:35.367
Geez, Mama.

01:14:35.367 --> 01:14:38.333
Well, you know Charlie,
I mean, he drinks a little.

01:14:38.333 --> 01:14:40.700
But hell, I knew that
when I married him.

01:14:40.700 --> 01:14:44.667
Other than that,
things are silky smooth.

01:14:44.667 --> 01:14:47.200
Course, when he drinks,
he's got a temper.

01:14:47.200 --> 01:14:48.734
Does he hit you?

01:14:48.734 --> 01:14:52.000
Just that one time.

01:14:54.433 --> 01:14:58.567
They say if a man hits you once,
there's always another time.

01:14:58.567 --> 01:15:02.533
Hey, sis, you have some money?
We want some more beer.

01:15:02.533 --> 01:15:04.166
Ooh, I wanna go with you.

01:15:04.166 --> 01:15:05.667
(chuckling)

01:15:05.667 --> 01:15:07.800
See you in a minute, Mama.

01:15:13.700 --> 01:15:16.867
You don't mean to tell me you
don't remember Barbara Simmons?

01:15:16.867 --> 01:15:19.633
You had crush on her all
through the fifth grade.

01:15:19.633 --> 01:15:21.934
Patsy, you're nothin'
but a damn liar.

01:15:21.934 --> 01:15:24.834
I don't know why, though,
with that frizzy brown hair.

01:15:24.834 --> 01:15:27.700
Well, what about you
and old Homer Atkinson?

01:15:27.700 --> 01:15:29.300
Homer Atkinson!

01:15:29.300 --> 01:15:30.834
I never liked
Homer Atkinson!

01:15:30.834 --> 01:15:33.166
You loved Homer Atkinson.
Oh! I did not!

01:15:33.166 --> 01:15:36.033
You used to call
him up every night...
You liar!

01:15:36.033 --> 01:15:38.133
And hang up when he answered.

01:15:38.133 --> 01:15:39.300
(tires screeching)
Look out!

01:15:49.767 --> 01:15:52.300
Somebody help me!

01:16:38.600 --> 01:16:42.333
The babies.

01:16:42.333 --> 01:16:44.100
Where are the babies?

01:16:44.100 --> 01:16:48.600
Patsy, they're fine.

01:16:48.600 --> 01:16:51.967
John's all right, too.

01:16:51.967 --> 01:16:54.967
You know, you had us scared
here a little bit.

01:16:56.667 --> 01:16:59.000
Tell me.

01:16:59.000 --> 01:17:02.700
Tell me,
are the babies alive?

01:17:02.700 --> 01:17:08.200
Honey, little Randy and
Julie weren't with you.

01:17:08.200 --> 01:17:11.934
John was with you,
and he's okay.

01:17:13.433 --> 01:17:15.433
Yeah.

01:17:15.433 --> 01:17:19.934
Shh, shh...

01:17:19.934 --> 01:17:24.934
Patsy:
♪ Moon in all your splendor
known only to my heart ♪

01:17:24.934 --> 01:17:29.767
♪ Call back my Rose,
Rose of San Antone ♪

01:17:29.767 --> 01:17:34.934
♪ Lips so sweet and tender
like petals fallin apart ♪

01:17:34.934 --> 01:17:36.467
♪ Speak once again... ♪

01:17:36.467 --> 01:17:38.133
Charlie, the kids
are sleeping.

01:17:38.133 --> 01:17:40.266
♪ Of my love, my own ♪

01:17:40.266 --> 01:17:44.433
♪ Broken song,
empty words I know ♪

01:17:44.433 --> 01:17:46.433
♪ Still live in my heart
all alone ♪

01:17:46.433 --> 01:17:48.900
Good night.

01:17:48.900 --> 01:17:54.367
♪ For that moonlit
pass by the Alamo ♪

01:17:54.367 --> 01:17:56.166
♪ And Rose my... ♪

01:18:07.734 --> 01:18:10.967
Just relax, now,
just a moment.

01:18:13.100 --> 01:18:14.967
Forceps, please.

01:18:21.967 --> 01:18:23.533
Very good.

01:18:23.533 --> 01:18:26.033
That's fine.

01:18:26.033 --> 01:18:27.367
That's very good.

01:18:27.367 --> 01:18:28.633
Fine, fine.

01:18:28.633 --> 01:18:30.667
Just as we expected.
It's healing nicely.

01:18:33.200 --> 01:18:35.266
Is it that bad?

01:18:35.266 --> 01:18:38.300
It's not that bad,
honey, it's just the stitches.
Let me look.

01:18:38.300 --> 01:18:40.400
When the stitches come out,

01:18:40.400 --> 01:18:42.834
the scars will heal
very quickly.

01:18:47.433 --> 01:18:50.400
So, this is what
I got to deal with, huh?

01:18:50.400 --> 01:18:52.166
Okay.

01:18:54.633 --> 01:18:57.800
Well, you cut your suit
to fit your cloth.

01:18:57.800 --> 01:19:00.500
Course, later you can have
plastic surgery if you want.

01:19:00.500 --> 01:19:03.166
(laughing)

01:19:03.166 --> 01:19:05.367
Hell, yes,
I want plastic surgery.

01:19:05.367 --> 01:19:07.567
I want all I can get.

01:19:07.567 --> 01:19:10.633
Maybe you can make me
look like Grace Kelly.

01:19:13.700 --> 01:19:16.000
Man:
♪ Crazy ♪

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:19.533
♪ Crazy for feelin'
so lonely ♪

01:19:21.500 --> 01:19:23.367
♪ I'm crazy ♪

01:19:23.367 --> 01:19:24.700
♪ Crazy for feelin' so blue ♪
Cut it!

01:19:24.700 --> 01:19:26.500
Cut it, please!

01:19:26.500 --> 01:19:28.166
Mr. Bradley...

01:19:28.166 --> 01:19:30.567
I don't care how many times
you play that,

01:19:30.567 --> 01:19:32.867
I can't sing
this man's songs.

01:19:32.867 --> 01:19:34.533
I don't know how
to sing like that.

01:19:34.533 --> 01:19:36.433
Nobody wants you to.

01:19:36.433 --> 01:19:37.967
You can take it
away from him.

01:19:37.967 --> 01:19:39.934
Yeah, the hell
with the demo.

01:19:39.934 --> 01:19:42.700
Steal the son of a bitch.

01:19:42.700 --> 01:19:44.533
I don't understand
why everything

01:19:44.533 --> 01:19:46.567
has to be so
goddamn hard, huh?

01:19:46.567 --> 01:19:48.066
How am I supposed
to do this now?

01:19:48.066 --> 01:19:50.333
Just like you
always do, Patsy.

01:19:50.333 --> 01:19:51.367
Your way.

01:19:51.367 --> 01:19:53.400
Let the song tell the story.

01:19:53.400 --> 01:19:55.700
(Intro to "Crazy" playing)

01:20:07.300 --> 01:20:09.800
♪ Crazy ♪

01:20:09.800 --> 01:20:14.066
♪ I'm crazy for feelin' ♪

01:20:14.066 --> 01:20:17.066
♪ So lonely ♪

01:20:19.700 --> 01:20:23.500
♪ I'm crazy ♪

01:20:23.500 --> 01:20:26.567
I think that's a good tempo.
Let's try it that way.

01:20:26.567 --> 01:20:28.900
Somebody bring me a beer!

01:20:28.900 --> 01:20:30.834
Will somebody bring
the lady a beer?

01:20:30.834 --> 01:20:32.767
Please.
Then we'll go for a take.

01:20:32.767 --> 01:20:34.700
(music playing)

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:40.266
♪ Wonderin' ♪

01:20:40.266 --> 01:20:49.333
♪ What in the world did I do ♪

01:20:49.333 --> 01:20:53.767
♪ Oh, crazy ♪

01:20:53.767 --> 01:20:57.767
♪ For thinkin' that my love ♪

01:20:57.767 --> 01:21:02.467
♪ Could hold you ♪

01:21:03.600 --> 01:21:07.567
♪ I'm crazy for tryin' ♪

01:21:07.567 --> 01:21:10.867
♪ And crazy for cryin' ♪

01:21:10.867 --> 01:21:16.500
♪ And I'm crazy
for lovin' you ♪

01:21:18.633 --> 01:21:21.367
♪ Crazy ♪

01:21:21.367 --> 01:21:27.633
♪ For thinkin' that
my love could hold you ♪

01:21:27.633 --> 01:21:30.433
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

01:21:30.433 --> 01:21:35.066
♪ I'm crazy for tryin' ♪

01:21:35.066 --> 01:21:38.834
♪ And crazy for cryin' ♪

01:21:38.834 --> 01:21:45.767
♪ And I'm crazy for lovin' ♪

01:21:45.767 --> 01:21:52.600
♪ You ♪♪

01:22:00.200 --> 01:22:03.834
Oh, God, honey,
I hope you like it!

01:22:03.834 --> 01:22:06.100
It's so pretty.

01:22:06.100 --> 01:22:07.600
There, there it is.

01:22:07.600 --> 01:22:09.600
See that white one up there
with the columns?

01:22:09.600 --> 01:22:10.867
(chuckling)

01:22:13.734 --> 01:22:15.533
Ain't it the truth?

01:22:17.033 --> 01:22:20.200
I fell in love with it
the minute I saw it.

01:22:20.200 --> 01:22:22.734
You know what I'd like?

01:22:22.734 --> 01:22:25.934
Just a real pale,
pale blue carpet.

01:22:25.934 --> 01:22:27.867
Maybe a couple divans.

01:22:27.867 --> 01:22:30.734
Make kind of a conversation
area, you know?

01:22:30.734 --> 01:22:33.100
(laughing)

01:22:33.100 --> 01:22:34.333
Hey, honey?

01:22:34.333 --> 01:22:38.467
Look at this.
We got a dishwasher.

01:22:38.467 --> 01:22:41.600
And an oven built
right into the wall.

01:22:41.600 --> 01:22:43.700
I want to check a roast,

01:22:43.700 --> 01:22:46.333
all I have to do is open
the door like this.

01:22:46.333 --> 01:22:48.000
No more bending over.

01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:49.967
The Queen of Sheba.

01:22:52.033 --> 01:22:53.567
Say you already bought it?

01:22:53.567 --> 01:22:55.767
Well, I paid down on it.

01:22:55.767 --> 01:22:58.133
Why didn't you tell me?

01:22:58.133 --> 01:23:00.367
I wanted to surprise you.

01:23:02.433 --> 01:23:03.934
You surprised me.

01:23:03.934 --> 01:23:06.633
Well, Randy says the best thing
we can do with our money now

01:23:06.633 --> 01:23:09.800
is put it in bricks and mortar.

01:23:16.800 --> 01:23:19.900
Oh, my Lord, that show
went on forever last night

01:23:19.900 --> 01:23:23.066
and every minute of it
shows in my face today.

01:23:25.600 --> 01:23:27.834
I'm glad we saved
"Crazy" till the end.

01:23:27.834 --> 01:23:30.300
I think it made
a great encore, don't you?

01:23:32.200 --> 01:23:34.633
Do you love Charlie?

01:23:34.633 --> 01:23:36.100
What?

01:23:36.100 --> 01:23:38.333
Do you love him?

01:23:38.333 --> 01:23:40.300
(chuckling)
Oh, come on.

01:23:40.300 --> 01:23:42.600
I couldn't get along
without Charlie.

01:23:42.600 --> 01:23:44.467
How's that song go?

01:23:44.467 --> 01:23:46.467
"He may have been a headache,
but he never was a bore."

01:23:46.467 --> 01:23:48.066
That's Charlie.

01:23:48.066 --> 01:23:49.834
Is that an answer?

01:23:51.700 --> 01:23:54.066
I think Charlie and
I deserve each other.

01:24:00.800 --> 01:24:03.400
Randy:
Looks like Charlie might be
throwing you a little party.

01:24:03.400 --> 01:24:04.967
Patsy: Sure does.

01:24:04.967 --> 01:24:06.000
Randy: Take care.

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:07.166
I'll see you
at the session.

01:24:07.166 --> 01:24:08.600
All right.

01:24:08.600 --> 01:24:11.333
Try and get a little sleep
between now and Friday!

01:24:11.333 --> 01:24:12.834
Nighty-night.

01:24:12.834 --> 01:24:15.100
Good night!

01:24:15.100 --> 01:24:17.333
(music playing)

01:24:27.500 --> 01:24:29.066
Miss Patsy Cline!

01:24:29.066 --> 01:24:30.600
In person!

01:24:30.600 --> 01:24:31.600
Hey, honey!

01:24:31.600 --> 01:24:33.433
My baby's home!

01:24:33.433 --> 01:24:34.900
I didn't expect
you home so early.

01:24:34.900 --> 01:24:36.533
We're having a party.
I see that.

01:24:36.533 --> 01:24:38.400
Did you see
my new car out there?

01:24:38.400 --> 01:24:40.533
I bought me an old
clunker for $75

01:24:40.533 --> 01:24:42.867
to drive in the demo
derby tomorrow night.

01:24:42.867 --> 01:24:45.000
Mmm... how are you?

01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:46.734
I think you know
most everybody.

01:24:46.734 --> 01:24:48.300
This here is, uh... Cindy.

01:24:48.300 --> 01:24:49.600
Hi there.

01:24:49.600 --> 01:24:51.300
John and Sarah
you know from work.

01:24:51.300 --> 01:24:53.900
That there's, uh...

01:24:53.900 --> 01:24:56.166
(laughing)
I don't know who that is.

01:24:56.166 --> 01:24:59.200
This is Skip Catmill.
He sold me that car.

01:24:59.200 --> 01:25:00.500
